<p class="no-box"><b>This will be updated frequently.</b><br>

<h3>Week One</h3><p class="no-box">March 29-April 2.
<ul>
<li><b>Class 1</b>:  Introduction to the course.  Introductory discussion of
  energy, conservation of energy, and power. 
<li><b>Lab 1</b>:  Measurement and watt meters.  Before lab sign up for a
  google account if you don't already have one.  You'll need this to
  use google docs. We'll be using google spreadsheets throughout the
  class. 
<li><b>Class 2</b>: Read Chapter 1 of SEWTHA.  Bring to class a few
  benchmarks about population and greenhouse gas emissions.  
</ul>
<br>



<h3>Week Two</h3><p class="no-box">April 5-9.
<ul>
<li><b>Class 3</b>: Different types of energy.  Electric current.
  Generating electricity.  
<li><b>Lab 2</b>: Build your own electric generator.
  class. 
<li><b>Class 4</b>: More units.  Estimation.  Different types of
  energy. 
</ul>
<br>



<h3>Week Three</h3><p class="no-box">April 12-15.
<ul>
<li><b>Class 5</b>: Solar energy basics.
<li><b>Lab 3</b>: Initial solar energy lab. 
  class. 
<li><b>Class 6</b>: Solar energy.
</ul>
<br>



<h3>Week Four</h3><p class="no-box">April 19-23.
<ul>
<li><b>Class 7</b>:  Wind power
<li><b>Lab 4</b>:  Wind power.
<li><b>Class 8</b>: Wind power
</ul>
<br>



<h3>Week Five</h3><p class="no-box">April 26-30.
